    "media:imagetext": "Jet\nSafety instructions\nAirbus A320 Overwing Exit\nEXITS TO BE OPERATED ONLY IN AN EMERGENCY\nBefore opening an exit, have a look through\nthe window to check outside\nDO NOT OPEN IF:\nSMOKE\nor\nsmoke is so thick\nyou can not see out,\nFIRE\nor\nthere is fire outside\nthe aircraft,\nOBSTRUCTIONS\nthere are\nobstructions.\nRemove handle cover\nThe slide armed indicator\nilluminates white\nPull down on the control handle\nThe exit moves inwards\nLift the exit from the frame\nDiscard the exit in the opposite\ndirection to the evacuation path\nIf the off wing escape slide fails\nto inflate automatically, pull the\nred manual inflation handle\nONCE ON THE GROUND MOVE AWAY FROM THE AIRCRAFT\nPLEASE DO NOT REMOVE THIS CARD FROM THE AIRCRAFT\nA320-0WBC01_1",
